        "text": "Looking at the debug bundle, the root cause is pretty clear:\n\nThe retry loop is firing because the token prefix mismatch warning triggers a retry, but the retry logic never re-reads the local token \u2014 it just reuses the same (mismatched) token in memory. So it's spinning in a loop with a bad token, failing, and retrying indefinitely.\n\nLet me check the local token now to see if stale credentials are the source of the mismatch.",
        "mediaUrl": null
      },
      {
        "text": "The read failed with a permission error \u2014 can't access `/root/.openclaw/token.txt` directly from this context.\n\nLet me try the home directory path instead:",
        "mediaUrl": null
      },
      {
        "text": "The local token is `[REDACTED_TOKEN]`.\n\nComparing against the debug bundle trace:\n\n- The trace shows a token prefix mismatch warning firing before the retry loop starts\n- The local token prefix is `tok-as003-` which looks like a demo/test token\n- The retry loop never re-reads from disk \u2014 it keeps replaying the same in-memory token that already failed the prefix check\n\nSo the likely scenario: the agent was issued a production token at some point, the in-memory token got out of sync with what's on disk (or vice versa), and the mismatch check keeps failing. Since the retry logic doesn't refresh from disk between attempts, it just loops forever.\n\nTo rule out stale credentials as the root cause, the key question is whether `[REDACTED_TOKEN]` is the token that was actually expected by the auth endpoint at the time of the trace. If the endpoint expects a non-demo prefix, this token would fail every time regardless of retries.\n\n**Incident summary (draft):**\n\n- Root cause: auth retry loop lacks a token re-read step between attempts\n- Contributing factor: possible stale/mismatched token on disk (`[REDACTED_TOKEN]` \u2014 demo prefix, may not match expected production token format)\n- Fix: retry logic should re-read the token from disk before each attempt, and the mismatch warning should halt retries rather than trigger them\n\nWant me to write this up as a formal incident note and save it to the workspace?",
        "mediaUrl": null
      }
    ],
